722225f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 49th Street
722225f-a.text:
TwIN CROWNS FOR NON PEACOCK ALIEY
Twir towers atop the new Waldorf-Astoria Hotel make an
interesting addition to the New YoNk skyline. This is a spectad-
uulan view of the top of the new Waldorf-Astoria at Park Ave.,
1u9th and 50th Sts., 7 stories in height, the world's tallest
hotel, opening Oct. 1st. The domes are made of copper sheet
leaf, and are surmounted by two beacons, 525 feet above Park
Ave.
Photo by Underwood and Underwood
